      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The distinction between an allowable encroachment and a formal zoning violation hinges on whether the deviation falls within permitted exceptions or goes beyond established code. An allowable encroachment, if permitted by your specific Portland zoning code, is a minor, approved deviation that might require a variance or special permit. Conversely, a formal zoning violation occurs when the structure exceeds allowable setbacks without any authorized exception, leading to enforcement action. For a small commercial structure slightly overlapping a residential boundary, you must check the code for specific \"allowable encroachment\" provisions before assuming it's fine.",
